article.headline: Kent St. 61, Texas A&amp,M-Corpus Christi 50
article.story: KENT, Ohio (AP) -- Haminn Quaintance had 13 points and 14 rebounds and Rodriquez Sherman scored 11 as Kent State never trailed in a 61-50 win Wednesday night over Texas A&M-Corpus Christi. The Golden Flashes (12-3) opened the game with a 12-4 run, capped by Quaintance's layup with 14:39 left in the half. The closest the Islanders came was 32-29 with 18:57 left in the game when Kevin Perkins hit a 3-pointer off a Quaintance turnover. Justin Reynolds and Isaiah Jackson each had 11 points to lead the Islanders (3-10), who shot 29 percent from the field. Kent State shot 40 percent.
